Kerr Spacetime Geodesic Generator documentation (WIP)

DEPENDENCIES:

Build:
valac
libjson-glib-dev
libgsl0-dev

Run:
vpython
matplotlib
jq
bc
imagemagick
ffmpeg


Sample usage:

1.	Build all the Vala executables, and test them

./build-all [fast]

ic=initial-conditions
data=/tmp/data
pot=/tmp/potential

./run-tests 2>/dev/null
rm -f $ic; ./rg2 2>/dev/null


2.	Run and plot one of the initial conditions files:

ic=ic/CircleUnStable
jq . $ic; ./bh3d.rk4 <$ic | ./plotBH.py `jq .M $ic` `jq .a $ic` &


3.	Generate initial conditions to stdout:
(PARAMETERS: min r, max r, min theta, spin, Lz multiplier)

./icgen dnewton 11.5 12.5 0.45 1.0 1.0 2>$pot



5.	Edit the inital conditions file and run again with tau and t as the time parameter:

./icgen dnewton 3.0 12.0 0.15 1.0 1.0 2>$pot | ./bh3d | ./finterp.py tau 0.5 | ./plotBH.py `jq .M $ic` `jq .a $ic`

./icgen.py 3.0 12.0 0.15 1.0 1.0 1.0 2>$pot | ./bh3d | ./finterp.py t 0.5 | ./plotBH.py `jq .M $ic` `jq .a $ic`


6.	Generate geodesic data and pass it to David Madore's kerr-image raytracer (ftp://ftp.madore.org/pub/madore/misc/kerr-image.c).

./icgen dnewton 3.0 12.0 0.15 1.0 1.0 2>$pot | ./bh3d.rk4 | ./raytrace-commands 0 2>/dev/null | ./raytrace


7.	Make a video out of the output files:

ffmpeg -y -i RaytracingOutput/%04d.png -c:v libx264 -crf 1 raytrace.mp4
mplayer raytrace.mp4 -fps 10


8.	Some example initial conditions pipelines . . .

./icgen dnewton 3.0 12.0 0.15 1.0 1.0 >$ic 2>$pot
./icgen dnewton 9.0 12.0 0.25 -1.0 1.0 >$ic 2>$pot

jq . $ic; ./bh3d.rk4 <$ic | ./plotBH.py `jq .M $ic` `jq .a $ic` &
jq . $ic; nc.openbsd pi 1234 <$ic | ./plotBH.py `jq .M $ic` `jq .a $ic` &

./icgen dnewton 3.0 12.0 0.15 1.0 2>$pot | ./bh3d.rk4 | ./raytrace-commands 0 2>/dev/null | ./raytrace


REFERENCE DATA

Particle trajectories

http://staff.science.nus.edu.sg/~phylyk/downloads/reports/sp2172_report.pdf

Light trajectories

http://www.physics.nus.edu.sg/~phyteoe/kerr/paper.pdf

